---
// src/components/ResponsiveHero.astro
---

<article class="w-full max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
  <div class="flex flex-col space-y-6">
    <span
      class="font-graphik-condensed text-fluid-meta font-bold tracking-expanded uppercase text-indigo-600 truncate"
    >
      Core Web Vitals Optimization Deployment.
    </span>

    <h1
      class="font-tiempos-fine text-fluid-display font-light tracking-display leading-display text-slate-950"
    >
      Balancing design elegance with absolute execution.
    </h1>

    <p
      class="font-graphik text-fluid-subhead font-medium tracking-normal leading-subhead text-slate-700"
    >
      Fluid type scaling handles your layout constraints dynamically. No rigid
      pixel breakpoints, no layout shifts, just clean performance parameters.
    </p>

    <div
      class="font-tiempos-text text-fluid-body leading-editorial text-slate-800 space-y-6 max-w-2xl"
    >
      <p>
        Continuous reading layouts demand tracking balance. By pairing a
        high-level system fallback configuration with fluid math rules, your
        mobile page components render instantaneously without forcing layout
        rewrites.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</article>
